    What is an avatar image?
    An avatar is a visual representation of a person for use in digital contexts. It's usually a computer-generated image, such as a bitmoji. On social media, the term “avatar” also refers to your profile picture—the image that represents you on the platform.

    Can an avatar be a photo?
    Avatars can be styled, colored and accessorized to suit the user's personality or preferences. A photograph of the user a cartoon or anime-style character, a 3D model, or even an animal or object can be used as an avatar.8 May 2023

    What is a avatar icon?
    In computing, an avatar is a graphical representation of a user, the user's character, or persona. Avatars can be two-dimensional icons in Internet forums and other online communities, where they are also known as profile pictures, userpics, or formerly picons (personal icons, or possibly "picture icons").
